    "legend": {
        "null": "Key is stripped from the payload before it reaches any table.",
        "item.* → items": "The item sub-object is resolved into the items table: item._id → items.item_uuid (UUID), item.code (via resultItemCode) → items.item_code_id, item.skills → items.primary_skill / secondary_skill, item.lastAcquisitionAt → items.last_acquisition_at. The FK transactions.item_id links the row to the items table.",
        "→ resultItemCode": "Added at runtime by prepare_transaction() in utils.py when item.code differs from itemCode. Used for skill classification and items.item_code_id. Not present in the raw API response.",
        "item_code_id vs items.item_code_id": "transactions.item_code_id stores what was traded / the case opened / the input material. items.item_code_id stores the actual item's code (which may differ, e.g., openCase: itemCode='case1', items.item_code_id='knife')."
